section.t:
This section describes how to define a new testcase. A new testcase should be described using the following parameters- Define testcase General description: describs why the particular test case is designed and the goal of the test case
Define desired behaviour from adaptation algorithm
Define matrix to evaluate the desired behaviours: indicates the mimimum set of metrics which are important for the proposed test case. But limited to the list.
Define test bed Test duration: defines the duration of the test.
Transport : defines transport level characteristics of a test case. Includes at least two sets of following link attributes one for forward direction and one for reverse direction. Path direction: {Forward, Reverse}
Number of bottlenecks: defines one or more bottleneck links
Bottleneck link speed: defienes the capacity of the bottleneck links
One-Way propagation delay: defines end to end oneway propagation delay
Maximum end to end jitter: defines maximum link jitter of the end to end path
Bottleneck queue type: {droptail,fq-codel,pie,...}
Bottleneck queue size in miliseconds:{20ms,...,1000ms}
Bottleneck link loss ratio: defines non-congestion related link losses.
Application: Defines different applications behaviour included in the test case Media Source: defines characteristics of media sources present in the test case. When using more than one media source if the media source characteristics varies then following set of attibutes must be defined for each such source types. Media direction: {Forward, Reverse}
Number of media sources: defines total number of media sources
Encoder configuration: defines how the media encoder behaves. This may include but not limited to Maximum Bitrate:{385kbps,....,2mpbs}
Minimum Bitrate:{100kbps, .....,300kbps}
Bitrate generation: {Constant bitrate,Variable bitrate}
Variation from target bitrate: {5%,....,15%}
Slagishness in bitrate change request:{10ms,....,1000ms}
Media content: defines types of encoded media content. for example for video one can use Foreman video sequence
Appearace preferece: Defines at what point of time in the test run the media source appears.
Startup behaviour: {slow start, maximum bitrate} in terms of kbps
Competing traffic source : defines characteristics of competing traffic source for the shared bottlenecks. A test case can Traffic direction:{Forward, Reverse}
Number of sources: defines total number of competing source of same type
Source types: defines the competing source type. for example whether it is a web browser or FTP download.
Adaptation algorithms: know adaptation algorithms used by the competing source type.
Appearace preferece:Defines at what point of time in the test run the media source appears
Other test specific setup: defines attributes those are a particular test specific and not included in this structure. This attributes should be well defines and should aid to understand the specific nature of the test case. It allows this stracture to be extended.

